conceal /kənˈsiːl/

(concealing,concealed,conceals) 

1. V-T If you conceal something, you cover it or hide it carefully. 掩盖; 隐藏 

例： Frances decided to conceal the machine behind a hinged panel. 弗朗西丝决定把那台机器藏到一块可开合的镶板后面。 

2. V-T If you conceal a piece of information or a feeling, you do not let other people know about it. 隐瞒 (信息); 掩饰 (情感) 

例： Robert could not conceal his relief. 罗伯特掩饰不住自己如释重负的心情。 

3. V-T If something conceals something else, it covers it and prevents it from being seen. 遮盖 

例： ...a pair of carved Indian doors which conceal a built-in cupboard. …一对遮挡嵌入壁橱的印度式雕花门。

